Diagnosis. (partly based on Carvalho & Cavichioli 2009 and Carvalho 2012 for
Paraportanus
): Crown ( Figs. 1 , 4, 11, 14, 21, 24) with anterior margin rounded. Crown, pronotum, and/or mesonotum ( Figs. 1 , 11, 21) usually marked with vibrant orange markings. Male pygofer (Figs. 5, 15, 25) strongly produced usually bearing pair of distinct spiniform processes on posteroventral margin. Subgenital plates (Figs. 6, 16, 26) triangular narrowing to apex; without unpigmented transverse line at basal third. Connective (Figs. 7, 17, 27) V- or Y-shaped with very short stalk.

